#Text=Ariane rocket launches Skynet and
#Text=Turksat spacecraft
#Text=Thursday , June 12 , 2008
#Text=An Ariane 5ECA rocket has successfully placed two communications satellites into Geosynchronous transfer orbit .
#Text=Liftoff , from ELA-3 at the Guiana Space Centre occurred at 22:05:02 GMT this evening .
#Text=The satellites launched were Skynet 5C , which will be used to relay secure communications for the British armed forces , and Turksat 3A , which will be used for commercial communications .
#Text=Paradigm Secure Communications
#Text=will operate Skynet 5C on behalf of Britain 's Ministry of Defence , whilst Turksat 3A will be operated by Turksat , an organisation based in Turkey .
#Text=The launch was conducted by French company Arianespace .
#Text=It was originally scheduled to occur in May , but was delayed when an incorrect guidance programme was found to have been installed on the rocket .

#Text=It is believed that several commands intended for use by the Ariane 5ES , a variant of the Ariane 5 used to launch spacecraft such as the Automated Transfer Vehicle , had been installed by mistake .
#Text=Skynet 5C and Turksat 3A separated from the carrier rocket 26 and 31 minutes after launch respectively , into a Geosynchronous transfer orbit .
#Text=They will perform burns of onboard engines to raise the perigees of their orbits , and inject into Geosynchronous orbits , approximately 35,000 kilometres above the equator .
#Text=Turksat 3A , which was constructed by Thales Alenia Space , will be positioned at a longitude of 42째E , where it will replace the older Turksat 1C satellite .
#Text=Skynet 5C , which was originally constructed as a backup spacecraft , will be placed at 17.8째W .
#Text=It was built by EADS Astrium .
#Text=This is the 30th orbital launch of 2008 , and the third to be conducted by an Ariane 5 rocket .
#Text=Overall , it is the 39th flight of an Ariane 5 , and the 14th flight of the ECA variant .
#Text=It is also the 25th successful launch of an Ariane rocket .
#Text=The flight designation for the launch was V184 , and the serial number of the rocket used was 540 .
#Text=The next Ariane 5 launch will occur in early July , with the Badr 6 and ProtoStar-1 satellites .
#Text=Speaking before launch , Arianespace Chairman Jean-Yves Le Gall described the mission as a " very important launch for us " .

#Text=Following launch , he said that he was " very happy to share this success with you " , and that Arianespace could make a " guarantee to Europe 's governments of their assured access to space " .

column1: #Text=He commented on the fact that this was Arianespace 's 25th consecutive successful launch , saying that this achievement " truly demands respect " .

#Text=Patrick Wood , the Skynet 5C programme director at Paradigm Secure Communications described the launch as " another great achievement , and another major milestone " , and that " we are extremely proud of it " .
#Text=Jean-Marie Robert , the manager of satellite programmes at Thales Alenia Space said that his company was " proud to have contributed " to the Turksat programme .
#Text=Binali Yildirim
#Text=, Turkey 's Minister of Transportation , made a speech via telephone , thanking Arianespace for the launch .
